  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To evaluate the influence of Plasma Rich in Growth Factors (PRGF) on the healing process of
      medial collateral ligament (MCL) tear.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Autologous platelet-rich matrices may aid in the healing of ligaments &amp; tendons by promoting
      and accelerating tissue healing because of the release of growth factors including
      transforming growth factor (TGF)-beta1 and platelet-derived growth factor (PDGF) from
      platelet alpha-granules.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
